FROM ubuntu:focal as build

# workaround tzdata install hanging
ENV TZ=Asia/Shanghai
RUN ln -snf /usr/share/zoneinfo/$TZ /etc/localtime && echo $TZ > /etc/timezone

RUN apt update
RUN apt install --no-install-recommends -y git gcc g++ make cmake autoconf automake libtool python3 libssl-dev && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*;
WORKDIR /kvrocks

COPY . .
RUN ./x.py build -DENABLE_OPENSSL=ON

FROM ubuntu:focal

RUN apt update && apt install --no-install-recommends -y libssl-dev && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*;

WORKDIR /kvrocks

COPY --from=build /kvrocks/build/kvrocks ./bin/

COPY ./kvrocks.conf  ./conf/
RUN sed -i -e 's%dir /tmp/kvrocks%dir /var/lib/kvrocks%g' ./conf/kvrocks.conf
VOLUME /var/lib/kvrocks

COPY ./LICENSE ./NOTICE ./DISCLAIMER ./
COPY ./licenses ./licenses

EXPOSE 6666:6666
ENTRYPOINT ["./bin/kvrocks", "-c", "./conf/kvrocks.conf"]
